#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Hardware tab"
msgstr "L'onglet Matériel"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:35
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The actual effect of setting these options depends upon the features "
#| "provided by your keyboard hardware and the X server on which &kde; is "
#| "running. As an example, you may find that changing the key click volume "
#| "has no effect because that feature is not available on your system."
msgid ""
"The actual effect of setting these options depends upon the features "
"provided by your keyboard hardware and the X server on which &plasma; is "
"running. As an example, you may find that changing the key click volume has "
"no effect because that feature is not available on your system."
msgstr ""
"Les effets que peuvent avoir ces options dépendent de votre clavier lui-même "
"et du serveur X sur lequel fonctionne &kde;. Il se peut par exemple que "
"changer le volume du petit bruit qui accompagne chaque appui sur une touche "
"ne soit pas possible car votre système ne le permet pas."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyboard model:"
msgstr "Modèle de clavier :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:45
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Here you can set your keyboard model. This setting is independent of your "
#| "keyboard layout and refers to the &quot;hardware&quot; model, i.e. the "
#| "way your keyboard is manufactured. Modern keyboards that come with your "
#| "computer usually have two extra keys and are referred to as &quot;104-"
#| "key&quot; models, which is probably what you want if you do not know what "
#| "kind of keyboard you have."
msgid ""
"Here you can set your keyboard model. This setting is independent of your "
"keyboard layout and refers to the &quot;hardware&quot; model, &ie; the way "
"your keyboard is manufactured. Modern keyboards that come with your computer "
"usually have two extra keys and are referred to as &quot;104-key&quot; "
"models, which is probably what you want if you do not know what kind of "
"keyboard you have."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez ici régler votre modèle de clavier. Ce réglage est indépendant "
"de votre disposition de clavier et se réfère au modèle matériel, c'est-à-"
"dire à la façon dont votre clavier est construit. Les claviers modernes "
"fournis avec votre ordinateur ont généralement deux touches supplémentaires "
"et on parle de modèle à &quot;104 touches&quot;, ce qui correspond "
"probablement à ce que vous voulez si vous ne connaissez pas votre modèle de "
"clavier."

